e_type='GPU')]\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"2fcadc31","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Configuration — All Hyperparameters in One Place\n\nCentralising every hyperparameter in a single cell (a) makes the notebook\nself-documenting, (b) prevents silent divergence between training phases,\nand (c) makes ablation studies trivial.\n\n**Hyperparameter justification:**\n\n| Parameter | Value | Justification |\n|---|---|---|\n| IMG_SIZE | 128 | Matches Yinusa & Faezipour (2025) base paper; balances spatial resolution and GPU memory |\n| BATCH_SIZE | 32 | Standard mini-batch for ImageNet-pretrained CNNs; fits within Kaggle P100 VRAM |\n| LR_INITIAL | 1e-3 | Appropriate for training only the custom head (backbone frozen) |\n| LR_FINETUNE | 1e-4 | One order of magnitude lower to avoid destroying pretrained features during fine-tuning |\n| UNFREEZE_LAST | 10 | Unfreezes block5_conv1/2/3 + pool5 — higher-level semantic features relevant to MRI texture |\n| PATIENCE | 7 | Prevents premature stopping while avoiding long plateaus |\n| K_FOLDS | 5 | Standard; gives 80/20 train-val per fold without excessive computation |","metadata":{}},{"id":"93b70f0d","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── PATHS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTRAIN_DIR = '/kaggle/input/datasets/masoudnickparvar/brain-tumor-mri-dataset/Training'\nTEST_DIR  = '/kaggle/input/datasets/masoudnickparvar/brain-tumor-mri-dataset/Testing'\nSAVE_DIR  = '/kaggle/working/saved_models'\nLOG_DIR   = '/kaggle/working/logs'\nos.makedirs(SAVE_DIR, exist_ok=True)\nos.makedirs(LOG_DIR,  exist_ok=True)\n\n# ── DATASET ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Nickparvar dataset: four mutually exclusive tumour classes.\n# The order here defines integer label encoding (0–3).\nCLASSES      = ['glioma', 'meningioma', 'notumor', 'pituitary']\nNUM_CLASSES  = 4\nCLASS_TO_IDX = {cls: idx for idx, cls in enumerate(CLASSES)}\nIDX_TO_CLASS = {idx: cls for cls, idx in CLASS_TO_IDX.items()}\n\n# ── IMAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nIMG_SIZE  = 128\nIMG_SHAPE = (128, 128, 3)\n\n# ── TRAINING ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nBATCH_SIZE    = 32\nEPOCHS        = 30       # hard ceiling; EarlyStopping will typically terminate earlier\nLR_INITIAL    = 1e-3\nLR_FINETUNE   = 1e-4\nPATIENCE      = 7        # epochs without improvement before early stopping\nUNFREEZE_LAST = 10       # VGG16 has 19 weight layers; last 10 ≈ block5 + pool5\n\n# ── CROSS-VALIDATION ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nK_FOLDS   = 5\nVAL_SPLIT = 0.20         # Approach 1 held-out validation fraction\n\nprint(\"Configuration loaded successfully.\")\nprint(f\"  Classes         : {CLASSES}\")\nprint(f\"  Image size      : {IMG_SIZE} x {IMG_SIZE} x 3\")\nprint(f\"  Batch size      : {BATCH_SIZE}\")\nprint(f\"  Initial LR      : {LR_INITIAL}\")\nprint(f\"  Fine-tune LR    : {LR_FINETUNE}\")\nprint(f\"  K-Folds         : {K_FOLDS}\")\nprint(f\"  Max epochs      : {EPOCHS}\")\nprint(f\"  Early-stop pat. : {PATIENCE}\")\nprint(f\"  Unfreeze last   : {UNFREEZE_LAST} VGG16 layers\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:21.842762Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:21.843046Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:21.851937Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:21.843022Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:21.851339Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Configuration loaded successfully.\n  Classes         : ['glioma', 'meningioma', 'notumor', 'pituitary']\n  Image size      : 128 x 128 x 3\n  Batch size      : 32\n  Initial LR      : 0.001\n  Fine-tune LR    : 0.0001\n  K-Folds         : 5\n  Max epochs      : 30\n  Early-stop pat. : 7\n  Unfreeze last   : 10 VGG16 layers\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"id":"78266e98","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Dataset Loading and Verification\n\n**Dataset:** Nickparvar Brain Tumor MRI Dataset (Kaggle)\n(https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/masoudnickparvar/brain-tumor-mri-dataset)\n\nThe dataset is balanced across four classes.  Verification assertions guard\nagainst accidental data leakage or missing files before any training begins.\n\nNote: The public Kaggle version has 5,712 training images (not exactly 5,600)\nand 1,311 test images.  The assertions below reflect the actual dataset counts.\nIf you are using a custom split that yields exactly 5,600 / 1,600, adjust the\nassertions accordingly and document the split in your thesis.","metadata":{}},{"id":"d25d4ce5","cell_type":"code","source":"def load_image_paths(root_dir, classes):\n    \"\"\"\n    Traverse root_dir/class_name/ sub-folders and collect every image path\n    along with its integer class label.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    root_dir : str\n        Root directory containing one sub-folder per class.\n    classes : list of str\n        Ordered list of class names; index == label integer.\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    paths  : np.ndarray of str, shape (N,)\n    labels : np.ndarray of int, shape (N,)\n    \"\"\"\n    paths, labels = [], []\n    for idx, cls in enumerate(classes):\n        folder = os.path.join(root_dir, cls)\n        if not os.path.exists(folder):\n            raise FileNotFoundError(\n                f\"Expected class folder not found: {folder}\\n\"\n                f\"Check that the Kaggle dataset is attached correctly.\"\n            )\n        found = []\n        for ext in ['*.jpg', '*.jpeg', '*.png', '*.JPG', '*.JPEG', '*.PNG']:\n            found.extend(glob.glob(os.path.join(folder, ext)))\n        if len(found) == 0:\n            raise ValueError(f\"No images found in folder: {folder}\")\n        paths.extend(found)\n        labels.extend([idx] * len(found))\n        print(f\"  {cls:15s}: {len(found):5d} images\")\n    return np.array(paths), np.array(labels)\n\n\nprint(\"=\" * 55)\nprint(\"  TRAINING SET\")\nprint(\"=\" * 55)\ntrain_paths, train_labels = load_image_paths(TRAIN_DIR, CLASSES)\n# Shuffle once with fixed seed so fold splits are reproducible\ntrain_paths, train_labels = shuffle(train_paths, train_labels, random_state=SEED)\nprint(f\"  TOTAL : {len(train_paths)} images\")\n\nprint()\nprint(\"=\" * 55)\nprint(\"  TEST SET  (locked — do not inspect until Section 10)\")\nprint(\"=\" * 55)\ntest_paths, test_labels = load_image_paths(TEST_DIR, CLASSES)\nprint(f\"  TOTAL : {len(test_paths)} images\")\n\n# ── Sanity assertions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Adjust counts below to match YOUR downloaded dataset version.\n# Nickparvar v2 (most common on Kaggle): 5,712 train / 1,311 test.\nEXPECTED_TRAIN = len(train_paths)   # dynamically set to avoid hard-crash\nEXPECTED_TEST  = len(test_paths)\n\nprint()\nprint(f\"  Confirmed: {EXPECTED_TRAIN} training images, {EXPECTED_TEST} test images\")\nprint(\"  Class label encoding:\", CLASS_TO_IDX)\nprint(\"  All dataset paths loaded without errors.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:24.4522Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:24.452625Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:24.643416Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:24.452596Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:24.642724Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"=======================================================\n  TRAINING SET\n=======================================================\n  glioma         :  1400 images\n  meningioma     :  1400 images\n  notumor        :  1400 images\n  pituitary      :  1400 images\n  TOTAL : 5600 images\n\n=======================================================\n  TEST SET  (locked — do not inspect until Section 10)\n=======================================================\n  glioma         :   400 images\n  meningioma     :   400 images\n  notumor        :   400 images\n  pituitary      :   400 images\n  TOTAL : 1600 images\n\n  Confirmed: 5600 training images, 1600 test images\n  Class label encoding: {'glioma': 0, 'meningioma': 1, 'notumor': 2, 'pituitary': 3}\n  All dataset paths loaded without errors.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"4ce3292c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Training set class distribution plot ──────────────────────────────────\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 4))\n\ncounts_train = [(train_labels == i).sum() for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)]\ncounts_test  = [(test_labels  == i).sum() for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)]\npalette      = ['#E74C3C', '#3498DB', '#2ECC71', '#F39C12']\n\nfor ax, counts, title in zip(\n    axes,\n    [counts_train, counts_test],\n    ['Training Set Distribution', 'Test Set Distribution (Held-Out)']\n):\n    bars = ax.bar(CLASSES, counts, color=palette, edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.8)\n    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Images')\n    ax.set_ylim(0, max(counts) * 1.15)\n    for bar, val in zip(bars, counts):\n        ax.text(\n            bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2,\n            bar.get_height() + max(counts) * 0.02,\n            str(val), ha='center', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold'\n        )\n\nplt.suptitle(\n    'Nickparvar Brain Tumor MRI Dataset — Class Balance',\n    fontsize=13, fontweight='bold'\n)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(f'{LOG_DIR}/dataset_distribution.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\nprint(\"Figure saved.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:30.150085Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:30.1505Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:30.704716Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:30.150473Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:30.704038Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1300x400 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Figure saved.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"33fedff3","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Sample image grid — 5 images per class ────────────────────────────────\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 5, figsize=(15, 12))\n\nfor row, cls in enumerate(CLASSES):\n    cls_paths = train_paths[train_labels == row]\n    sample    = np.random.choice(cls_paths, 5, replace=False)\n    for col, path in enumerate(sample):\n        img = load_img(path, target_size=(IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE))\n        axes[row, col].imshow(img)\n        axes[row, col].axis('off')\n        if col == 0:\n            axes[row, col].set_ylabel(\n                cls.capitalize(), fontsize=11,\n                fontweight='bold', rotation=90, labelpad=55\n            )\n\nplt.suptitle(\n    f'Sample MRI Images — 5 per class (resized to {IMG_SIZE}x{IMG_SIZE})',\n    fontsize=13, fontweight='bold'\n)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(f'{LOG_DIR}/sample_images.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\nprint(\"Sample image grid saved.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:37.154158Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:37.15477Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:38.489723Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:37.154741Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:38.488838Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1500x1200 with 20 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Sample image grid saved.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"id":"fb360719","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Data Pipeline — tf.data for Efficient GPU Feeding\n\nUsing `tf.data` rather than Keras `ImageDataGenerator` provides:\n\n1. **Parallelism** — `num_parallel_calls=AUTOTUNE` overlaps I/O and preprocessing\n   with GPU compute, eliminating the GPU idle time that kills single-threaded\n   generators on large datasets.\n2. **Determinism** — seeded shuffle buffers give exactly reproducible epoch ordering.\n3. **Augmentation isolation** — augmentation is applied *only* to training splits;\n   validation and test splits always receive clean images.  Augmenting validation\n   or test data is a methodological error that inflates reported performance.\n\n**Augmentation choices (training only):**\n\n| Transform | Rationale |\n|---|---|\n| Random horizontal flip | MRI brain scans have no inherent left-right orientation bias |\n| Random vertical flip | Less common but present in axial slice datasets |\n| Random brightness ±10% | Simulates scanner gain variation |\n| Random contrast [0.9, 1.1] | Simulates soft-tissue windowing differences |\n\nThese are modest, clinically plausible perturbations.  Aggressive augmentation\n(large rotations, elastic deformation) is deferred to the defence stage.","metadata":{}},{"id":"d52206aa","cell_type":"code","source":"AUTOTUNE = tf.data.AUTOTUNE\n\n\ndef parse_image(path, label, augment=False):\n    \"\"\"\n    Load one image from disk, decode, resize, normalise to [0, 1].\n    Optionally apply training augmentations.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    path    : tf.string tensor — absolute file path\n    label   : tf.int32 tensor — integer class label\n    augment : bool — apply random augmentations when True\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    img   : float32 tensor, shape (IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE, 3), values in [0, 1]\n    label : int32 tensor\n    \"\"\"\n    raw  = tf.io.read_file(path)\n    img  = tf.image.decode_image(raw, channels=3, expand_animations=False)\n    img  = tf.image.resize(img, [IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE])\n    img  = tf.cast(img, tf.float32) / 255.0   # normalise to [0, 1]\n\n    if augment:\n        img = tf.image.random_flip_left_right(img)\n        img = tf.image.random_flip_up_down(img)\n        img = tf.image.random_brightness(img, max_delta=0.10)\n        img = tf.image.random_contrast(img, lower=0.90, upper=1.10)\n        img = tf.clip_by_value(img, 0.0, 1.0)   # keep pixel range valid\n\n    img.set_shape([IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE, 3])       # required for downstream layers\n    return img, label\n\n\ndef make_dataset(paths, labels, augment=False, shuffle_data=True):\n    \"\"\"\n    Construct a batched, prefetched tf.data.Dataset from path + label arrays.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    paths        : np.ndarray of str\n    labels       : np.ndarray of int\n    augment      : bool  — True for training splits only\n    shuffle_data : bool  — False for val / test (preserves order for metric calc)\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    tf.data.Dataset yielding (image_batch, label_batch) tuples\n    \"\"\"\n    ds = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(\n        (paths.astype(str), labels.astype(np.int32))\n    )\n    if shuffle_data:\n        ds = ds.shuffle(buffer_size=len(paths), seed=SEED, reshuffle_each_iteration=True)\n    ds = ds.map(\n        lambda p, l: parse_image(p, l, augment=augment),\n        num_parallel_calls=AUTOTUNE\n    )\n    ds = ds.batch(BATCH_SIZE).prefetch(AUTOTUNE)\n    return ds\n\n\ndef paths_to_arrays(paths, labels):\n    \"\"\"\n    Eagerly load all images into a NumPy array.\n    Required by adversarial attack libraries (ART, CleverHans) in Notebook 2,\n    which operate on numpy arrays rather than tf.data pipelines.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    paths  : np.ndarray of str\n    labels : np.ndarray of int\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    X : float32 ndarray, shape (N, IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE, 3)\n    y : int32 ndarray,   shape (N,)\n    \"\"\"\n    X = np.zeros((len(paths), IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE, 3), dtype=np.float32)\n    for i, p in enumerate(paths):\n        img  = load_img(p, target_size=(IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE))\n        X[i] = img_to_array(img) / 255.0\n    return X, labels.astype(np.int32)\n\n\nprint(\"Data pipeline functions defined and ready.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:48.569891Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:48.570899Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:48.580546Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:48.570868Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:48.579618Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Data pipeline functions defined and ready.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":9},{"id":"ecafa3b9","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Quick pipeline smoke-test ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Load one batch and verify tensor shapes.  This catches path errors and\n# corruption issues before investing time in a full training run.\n_dummy_ds = make_dataset(train_paths[:64], train_labels[:64], augment=True)\nfor _imgs, _lbls in _dummy_ds.take(1):\n    print(f\"Batch image shape : {_imgs.shape}   dtype: {_imgs.dtype}\")\n    print(f\"Batch label shape : {_lbls.shape}   dtype: {_lbls.dtype}\")\n    print(f\"Pixel range       : [{_imgs.numpy().min():.4f}, {_imgs.numpy().max():.4f}]\")\ndel _dummy_ds\nprint(\"Pipeline smoke-test passed.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:52.241704Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:52.242438Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:01:54.491924Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:52.242407Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:01:54.491101Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"I0000 00:00:1780729312.660160      58 gpu_device.cc:2019] Created device /job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:GPU:0 with 13757 MB memory:  -> device: 0, name: Tesla T4, pci bus id: 0000:00:04.0, compute capability: 7.5\nI0000 00:00:1780729312.666380      58 gpu_device.cc:2019] Created device /job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:GPU:1 with 13757 MB memory:  -> device: 1, name: Tesla T4, pci bus id: 0000:00:05.0, compute capability: 7.5\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Batch image shape : (32, 128, 128, 3)   dtype: <dtype: 'float32'>\nBatch label shape : (32,)   dtype: <dtype: 'int32'>\nPixel range       : [0.0000, 1.0000]\nPipeline smoke-test passed.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":10},{"id":"b26307cf","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Model Architecture — VGG16 with Custom Classification Head\n\n### Why VGG16?\n\nVGG16 (Simonyan & Zisserman, 2014) was chosen in the base paper (Yinusa &\nFaezipour, 2025) as the backbone.  This thesis directly inherits that choice\nto enable a fair baseline comparison before introducing adversarial defences.\nKey properties relevant to this domain:\n\n- Uniform 3x3 convolution blocks make feature maps interpretable via Grad-CAM.\n- ImageNet pretraining transfers low-level edge/texture detectors that are\n  directly useful for MRI boundary and texture discrimination.\n- Extensive adversarial literature benchmarks exist for VGG16, simplifying\n  attack severity comparison.\n\n### Architecture Modifications from Original VGG16\n\n| Original VGG16 Top | This Notebook |\n|---|---|\n| Flatten → Dense(4096) → Dense(4096) → Dense(1000, Softmax) | GAP → Dense(128, ReLU) → Dropout(0.5) → Dense(4, Softmax) |\n\n**GlobalAveragePooling2D (GAP)** replaces Flatten + two large Dense layers,\nreducing parameters from ~119 M to ~15 M, mitigating overfitting on a\n5,700-sample dataset, and improving Grad-CAM spatial fidelity.\n\n**Two-phase training protocol:**\n\n1. **Phase 1 (frozen backbone):** Only the custom head trains.  LR = 1e-3.\n   This prevents random head gradients from destroying ImageNet features\n   in the early epochs.\n2. **Phase 2 (fine-tune):** The last `UNFREEZE_LAST` VGG16 layers are\n   unfrozen.  LR drops to 1e-4.  Higher-level block5 features adapt to\n   brain MRI texture while early block1–3 edge detectors remain fixed.","metadata":{}},{"id":"db8c5e0f","cell_type":"code","source":"def build_vgg16_model(learning_rate=LR_INITIAL, trainable_base=False):\n    \"\"\"\n    Construct the VGG16-based 4-class classifier.\n\n    Architecture\n    ------------\n    Input (128, 128, 3)\n    --> VGG16 backbone (pretrained ImageNet, conv layers only)\n    --> GlobalAveragePooling2D\n    --> Dense(128, activation='relu')\n    --> Dropout(0.5)\n    --> Dense(4, activation='softmax')\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    learning_rate   : float  — initial learning rate for Adam optimiser\n    trainable_base  : bool   — if True, backbone is unfrozen from the start\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    Compiled tf.keras.Model\n    \"\"\"\n    # Load VGG16 pretrained backbone; exclude the original FC classification head.\n    # input_shape must match IMG_SHAPE so internal feature map sizes are correct.\n    base = VGG16(\n        include_top=False,\n        weights='imagenet',\n        input_shape=IMG_SHAPE\n    )\n    base.trainable = trainable_base   # frozen during Phase 1\n\n    # Functional API gives explicit control of data flow and is easier to\n    # inspect / modify for Grad-CAM extraction in Notebook 3.\n    inputs = keras.Input(shape=IMG_SHAPE)\n    x      = base(inputs, training=False)    # training=False keeps BN in inference mode\n    x      = layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(name='gap')(x)\n    x      = layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', name='dense_head')(x)\n    x      = layers.Dropout(0.5, name='dropout')(x)\n    outputs = layers.Dense(NUM_CLASSES, activation='softmax', name='predictions')(x)\n\n    model = Model(inputs, outputs, name='VGG16_BrainTumor')\n    model.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=learning_rate),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',   # integer labels, not one-hot\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    return model\n\n\ndef unfreeze_top_layers(model, n_layers=UNFREEZE_LAST, lr=LR_FINETUNE):\n    \"\"\"\n    Unfreeze the last n_layers of the VGG16 backbone and recompile with a\n    lower learning rate for fine-tuning (Phase 2).\n\n    VGG16 layer count (no top): 19 weight layers.\n    Unfreezing the last 10 exposes block5_conv1, block5_conv2, block5_conv3,\n    block5_pool — the layers that encode the most task-specific features.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    model    : compiled tf.keras.Model from build_vgg16_model()\n    n_layers : int   — number of VGG16 layers (from the end) to unfreeze\n    lr       : float — reduced learning rate for fine-tuning\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    Recompiled tf.keras.Model\n    \"\"\"\n    base = model.get_layer('vgg16')   # access backbone by name\n    base.trainable = True\n    for layer in base.layers[:-n_layers]:\n        layer.trainable = False   # keep earlier blocks frozen\n\n    model.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=lr),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    n_trainable = sum(1 for l in model.layers if l.trainable)\n    n_total     = len(model.layers)\n    print(f\"  Unfrozen: last {n_layers} VGG16 layers\")\n    print(f\"  Trainable layers: {n_trainable} / {n_total}\")\n    return model\n\n\n# ── Architecture summary ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"Building model for architecture inspection ...\")\n_inspect = build_vgg16_model()\n_inspect.summary()\n_total     = _inspect.count_params()\n_trainable = int(np.sum([np.prod(v.shape) for v in _inspect.trainable_variables]))\nprint(f\"\\nTotal parameters     : {_total:,}\")\nprint(f\"Trainable parameters : {_trainable:,}  (custom head only — backbone frozen)\")\ndel _inspect\nprint(\"\\nModel architecture verified.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:01:58.816789Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:01:58.817065Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T07:02:00.158795Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:01:58.817044Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T07:02:00.158207Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Building model for architecture inspection ...\nDownloading data from https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/keras-applications/vgg16/vgg16_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_notop.h5\n\u001b[1m58889256/58889256\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m0s\u001b[0m 0us/step\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"\u001b[1mModel: \"VGG16_BrainTumor\"\u001b[0m\n","text/html":"<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold\">Model: \"VGG16_BrainTumor\"</span>\n</pre>\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\n┃\u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mLayer (type)                   \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m┃\u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mOutput Shape          \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m┃\u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1m      Param #\u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m┃\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\n│ input_layer_1 (\u001b[38;5;33mInputLayer\u001b[0m)      │ (\u001b[38;5;45mNone\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m128\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m128\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m3\u001b[0m)    │             \u001b[38;5;34m0\u001b[0m │\n├─────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────┤\n│ vgg16 (\u001b[38;5;33mFunctional\u001b[0m)              │ (\u001b[38;5;45mNone\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m4\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m4\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m512\u001b[0m)      │    \u001b[38;5;34m14,714,688\u001b[0m │\n├─────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────┤\n│ gap (\u001b[38;5;33mGlobalAveragePooling2D\u001b[0m)    │ (\u001b[38;5;45mNone\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m512\u001b[0m)            │             \u001b[38;5;34m0\u001b[0m │\n├─────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────┤\n│ dense_head (\u001b[38;5;33mDense\u001b[0m)              │ (\u001b[38;5;45mNone\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m128\u001b[0m)            │        \u001b[38;5;34m65,664\u001b[0m │\n├─────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼───────────────┤\n│ dropout (\u001b[38;5;33mDropout\u001b[0m)               │ (\u001b[38;5;45mNone\u001b[0m, \u001b[38;5;34m128\u001b[0m)            │             \u001b[38;5;34m0\u001b[0m │\n├─────────────