856    0.9786    0.9821       280\n     notumor     0.9859    0.9964    0.9911       280\n   pituitary     1.0000    0.9929    0.9964       280\n\n    accuracy                         0.9902      1120\n   macro avg     0.9902    0.9902    0.9902      1120\nweighted avg     0.9902    0.9902    0.9902      1120\n\n  Confusion matrix saved: /kaggle/working/logs/A1_val_confusion_matrix.png\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1400x500 with 4 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":16},{"id":"a45021c6","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 8. Approach 2 + 3 — 5-Fold Stratified Cross-Validation\n\n### Why K-Fold CV?\n\nA single train/val split (Approach 1) cannot distinguish between a model\nthat is genuinely good and one that happened to receive easy images in its\nvalidation set.  5-fold stratified CV:\n\n- Uses 100% of training data for both training and validation (at different folds)\n- Provides a mean accuracy and standard deviation, quantifying stability\n- Reduces selection bias in the reported performance\n\nThe same two-phase training protocol is applied independently within each fold.\nThe test set remains completely unseen throughout all K folds.\n\n### Best Fold Selection (Approach 3)\n\nAfter CV, the fold whose best checkpoint achieved the highest validation\naccuracy is loaded and evaluated exactly **once** on the test set.\nThis is a standard protocol in medical imaging literature to report\ngeneralisation performance without overfitting to the test set.","metadata":{}},{"id":"f577b93c","cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"  APPROACH 2 + 3: 5-Fold Stratified Cross-Validation\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\n\nskf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=K_FOLDS, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\n\nfold_results = []   # list of dicts, one per fold\nall_val_true = []\nall_val_pred = []\n\nfor fold_idx, (train_idx, val_idx) in enumerate(skf.split(train_paths, train_labels)):\n    fold_num = fold_idx + 1\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  FOLD {fold_num} / {K_FOLDS}\")\n    print(f\"  Train samples: {len(train_idx)}   |   Val samples: {len(val_idx)}\")\n\n    fold_train_paths  = train_paths[train_idx]\n    fold_train_labels = train_labels[train_idx]\n    fold_val_paths    = train_paths[val_idx]\n    fold_val_labels   = train_labels[val_idx]\n\n    print(\"  Val class distribution:\")\n    for i, cls in enumerate(CLASSES):\n        print(f\"    {cls:15s}: {(fold_val_labels == i).sum()}\")\n\n    # Build tf.data datasets for this fold\n    fold_train_ds = make_dataset(fold_train_paths, fold_train_labels, augment=True,  shuffle_data=True)\n    fold_val_ds   = make_dataset(fold_val_paths,   fold_val_labels,   augment=False, shuffle_data=False)\n\n    # ── Phase 1: Frozen backbone ──────────────────────────────────────────\n    print(f\"\\n  Phase 1: Frozen backbone training ...\")\n    model      = build_vgg16_model(learning_rate=LR_INITIAL, trainable_base=False)\n    cbs_p1, ckpt_p1 = get_callbacks(fold_id=fold_num, phase='initial')\n\n    hist_p1 = model.fit(\n        fold_train_ds,\n        validation_data=fold_val_ds,\n        epochs=EPOCHS,\n        callbacks=cbs_p1,\n        verbose=0   # suppress per-epoch output for cleaner multi-fold logs\n    )\n    print(f\"  Phase 1 best val_accuracy: \"\n          f\"{max(hist_p1.history['val_accuracy']):.4f} \"\n          f\"(epoch {np.argmax(hist_p1.history['val_accuracy'])+1})\")\n\n    # ── Phase 2: Fine-tune ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    print(f\"  Phase 2: Fine-tuning (last {UNFREEZE_LAST} VGG16 layers) ...\")\n    model      = unfreeze_top_layers(model, n_layers=UNFREEZE_LAST, lr=LR_FINETUNE)\n    cbs_p2, ckpt_p2 = get_callbacks(fold_id=fold_num, phase='finetune')\n\n    hist_p2 = model.fit(\n        fold_train_ds,\n        validation_data=fold_val_ds,\n        epochs=EPOCHS,\n        callbacks=cbs_p2,\n        verbose=0\n    )\n    print(f\"  Phase 2 best val_accuracy: \"\n          f\"{max(hist_p2.history['val_accuracy']):.4f} \"\n          f\"(epoch {np.argmax(hist_p2.history['val_accuracy'])+1})\")\n\n    # ── Restore best checkpoint ───────────────────────────────────────────\n    model = tf.keras.models.load_model(ckpt_p2)\n\n    # ── Evaluate this fold ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    fold_eval = evaluate_model(\n        model, fold_val_paths, fold_val_labels,\n        dataset_name=f'Fold {fold_num} Validation'\n    )\n\n    plot_training_history(\n        hist_p2, fold_id=fold_num, phase='finetune',\n        save_path=f'{LOG_DIR}/fold{fold_num}_finetune_history.png'\n    )\n    plot_confusion_matrix(\n        fold_eval['y_true'], fold_eval['y_pred'],\n        title=f'Fold {fold_num} Confusion Matrix',\n        save_path=f'{LOG_DIR}/fold{fold_num}_confusion_matrix.png'\n    )\n\n    fold_results.append({\n        'fold'         : fold_num,\n        'val_accuracy' : fold_eval['accuracy'],\n        'val_f1'       : fold_eval['f1'],\n        'checkpoint'   : ckpt_p2,\n        'y_true'       : fold_eval['y_true'],\n        'y_pred'       : fold_eval['y_pred'],\n    })\n    all_val_true.extend(fold_eval['y_true'])\n    all_val_pred.extend(fold_eval['y_pred'])\n\n    # Free GPU memory before next fold\n    tf.keras.backend.clear_session()\n    print(f\"\\n  Fold {fold_num} complete | Val accuracy: {fold_eval['accuracy']:.4f}\")\n\nprint(\"\\n  All folds complete.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-06T07:18:00.556874Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-06T07:18:00.55719Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-06T08:29:47.214296Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-06T07:18:00.557168Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-06T08:29:47.21342Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"============================================================\n  APPROACH 2 + 3: 5-Fold Stratified Cross-Validation\n============================================================\n\n===================================